From: dominicg <dominicg@brax3.local>
Date: Sat, 18 Jul 2026 16:59:18 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 5/7] brax3: META snWriter backup timeout - root cause +
 APEXFIX state (WIP)

Root-caused the snWriter final-step timeout (REQ_BackupNvram2BinRegion /
SP_META_SetCleanBootFlag_r) end-to-end. IMEI provisioning itself works under
enforcing; the failure is the modem clean-boot confirmation.

Chain: meta_tst blocks reading the CCCI modem port for SetCleanBootFlag
confirmation, modem needs RPMB secure storage, RPMB/TEE fail, keystore2 AND
TeeMcDaemon crash on link ("libandroidicu.so not found ... namespace default"),
vold cannot unwrap FBE, /data never mounts. keystore2 needs the FULL linkerconfig
(com.android.i18n apex libs) which perform_apex_config generates at post-fs-data,
AFTER late-fs; mount_all --late deadlocks before reaching it. Circular; an
A13->A15/16 regression (works on the A13 BSP, not iode A15/16).

Kept (real fix): apex-info-list relabel makes META healthy (IMEI + modem NVRAM
work). See the system/sepolicy commit.

Reverted: Option A (start keystore2 + mount_all --late) - DEADLOCKS on A15/16.
Staying on APEXFIX: no keystore2, raw ext4 /data mount (fails harmlessly).

Diagnostic scaffolding (REMOVE before merge): init/brax-metadiag.sh + its
sh_binary/PRODUCT_PACKAGES wiring - dumps kernel stacks + logs to
/mnt/vendor/nvdata during META for backup diagnosis.

Full detail: BSP docs/07-snwriter-meta-worklog.md (2026-07-18 session 2).

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>
